    <section class="key-terms" id="sect-00005">
      <title>Key Terms</title>
      <list bullet-style="bulleted" id="list-00003">
      <item>credit score</item>
      <item>revolving credit</item>
      <item>installment credit</item>
      <item>open credit</item>
      <item>credit report</item>
      </list>
      </section>
      <section class="key-concepts" id="sect-00006">
        <title>Key Concepts</title>
      <list bullet-style="bulleted" id="list-00004">
      <item>Your credit score is one of the most important numbers in your life. It is the basis of whether you will qualify to buy a house, a car, get a credit card, and perhaps even a job. There are many different items that play a part in determining your credit score, past credit history being one of the most important.</item>
      <item>There are three types of credit accounts: revolving, installment and open.</item>
      <item>An acceptable credit score starts ranges from about 690 to 850.</item>
      </list>
      </section>
